The paper deals with the space complexity of solving linear systems of equations, which is a fundamental problem in computational complexity theory. The use of Laplacian matrices of graphs is a common technique in computer science, particularly in the analysis of algorithms and networks. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely categories. The paper also involves the analysis of graphs, which suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as another possible category. The use of numerical methods and the estimation of eigenvalues suggest cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as a possible category. Finally, the paper involves the analysis of quantum algorithms, which suggests cs.SI (Systems and Control) as a possible category.
